                <div class="col-lg-8">
                    <div id="general" class="rule-card mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                        <div class="rule-header">
                            <span class="rule-num">01</span>
                            <h3>General Rules</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="rule-body">
                            <ul class="rules-list mb-0">
                                <li>Pupils with proper uniform must reach the school premises at least 10 minutes before
                                    the bell rings.</li>
                                <li>To acquire proficiency in English, English and only English is permissible within
                                    the school premises.</li>
                                <li>The reason for leave of absence must be entered by the guardians in the leave of
                                    absence diary. Leave of absence for more than three days should be applied for
                                    separately to the Principal through the Class Teacher.</li>

                                <div class="hidden-li-content" style="display: none;">
                                    <li>A pupil who has been absent from class for more than three days may attend class
                                        only after leave of absence has been granted by the Principal in the absence
                                        record. No late comer shall be allowed to attend the school on any pretext.</li>
                                    <li>Pupils must rejoin classes after the holidays on reopening days.</li>
                                    <li>Any communication (request or complaint) made by the parents should be addressed
                                        to the Principal.</li>
                                    <li>During break time, pupils shall not be allowed to go out of the school premises.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Pupils who do not have at least 75% attendance may not be allowed to appear in
                                        the examination.</li>
                                    <li>Students are advised to use their home address for all mails directed to them.
                                        The Principal reserves the right to open the mail of pupils who use the school
                                        address. Letters addressed to pupils with the school address may not be
                                        delivered.</li>
                                    <li>A student is liable to be removed from the class register or otherwise dealt
                                        with by the school authority for irregular attendance, habitual negligence in
                                        studies, disobedience, or any conduct detrimental to the interest of the school.
                                        If parents or legal guardians fail to withdraw their ward within a week after
                                        receiving written notice, the student’s name will be struck off from the class
                                        register without further reference.</li>
                                    <li>Any damage done to school building or furniture by the student shall be made
                                        good by the parents or legal guardians of the pupil concerned. The Principal’s
                                        decision regarding compensation shall be final.</li>
                                    <li>Pupils are responsible for the safe custody of their books, umbrellas,
                                        raincoats, etc. The school takes no responsibility for loss of these items.</li>
                                    <li>Smoking and the use of tobacco in any form are strictly forbidden. Offenders
                                        will be punished and expelled from the school.</li>
                                    <li>Any undemocratic attitude or agitation towards the school is not permissible.
                                    </li>
                                    <li>Parents and guardians are not allowed to see their children or meet teachers
                                        during school hours without prior permission from the Principal.</li>
                                    <li>No student will be allowed to deposit tuition fees during class hours.</li>
                                    <li>No student will be granted leave after certain periods. In case of emergency,
                                        the school will notify the guardian.</li>
                                    <li>Guardians may meet the Principal between 10:30 A.M. to 11:30 A.M. from Monday to
                                        Friday on working days. No guardian will be entertained before or after the
                                        fixed time.</li>
                                    <li>Pupils suffering from contagious or infectious diseases shall not be permitted
                                        to attend school.</li>
                                    <li>No student will be allowed to enter the school complex with a cell phone.</li>
                                </div>
                            </ul>

                            <div class="text-center mt-4 pt-3 border-top">
                                <button onclick="toggleList(this)"
                                    class="btn btn-navy rounded-pill px-4 shadow-sm rulesBtn">
                                    Read All Rules <i class="bi bi-chevron-down ms-2"></i>
                                </button>
                            </div>

                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div id="admission" class="rule-card mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                        <div class="rule-header">
                            <span class="rule-num">02</span>
                            <h3>Admission & Withdrawal</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="rule-body">
                            <ul class="rules-list mb-0">
                                <p>
                                    New admission is open to all at the K.G.-I level. Registration of the names of wards
                                    must be completed within the dates notified by the school authority using the
                                    prescribed forms. Admission to other classes up to Class IX depends on the
                                    availability of seats as notified by the authority. Selection for admission is made
                                    on the basis of admission tests and merit. For new admissions, production of a birth
                                    certificate from the appropriate authority is compulsory.
                                </p>

                                <div class="hidden-li-content" style="display: none;">
                                    <p>
                                        A pupil having a valid transfer certificate from a recognized school may be
                                        admitted on the basis of an admission test, subject to the availability of
                                        seats. Registration of the name of the intending candidate with the school
                                        office in the prescribed form is mandatory. Parades held on special occasions
                                        such as Independence Day and Republic Day are considered an integral part of
                                        co-curricular activities.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Pupils found to have obtained admission through false representation will be
                                        struck off from the school, and the matter will be reported to the Inspector of
                                        Schools for appropriate action. Applications for a Transfer Certificate may be
                                        made only by parents or legal guardians and must be submitted at least 30 days
                                        in advance.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        No pupil whose fees are in arrears upto a term will be given a transfer
                                        certificate. T.C. required after the new session starts will be issued only on
                                        payment of full tuition fees for the academic year. No pupil who fails in two
                                        consecutive years in the same class shall be allowed to continue his studies in
                                        the school. A pupil who has left the school will not normally be readmitted.
                                    </p>
                                    <p><strong>ADMISSION TEST</strong></p>
                                    <p>
                                        a) Admission in Nursery as per norms.
                                        b) Admission in K.G.-I is based on oral test only.
                                        c) Admission in K.G.-II to Class IX will be on the basis of both written and
                                        oral test subject to availability of seats.
                                    </p>
                                    <p><strong>EXAMINATION</strong></p>
                                    <p>Besides the Unit Tests, there are two examinations in the year, Half-Yearly and
                                        Annual Examination. The Unit test/monthly Unit Test, Half-Yearly and Annual Exam
                                        will be taken into account towards promotions to the next higher class. Hence
                                        the pupils are advised to take them seriously.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        Absence from an examination on medical ground should be intimated to the
                                        Headmaster immediately during the examination supported by valid Medical
                                        Certificate.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Anyone adopting unfair means in examination will be put under necessary
                                        penalisation as the school authority may deem fit. The decision of the school
                                        authority is final.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Promotion to the next higher class depends on the overall performance of the
                                        students during the whole year. From weightage to the extent of 20% of Unit
                                        test, 30% of Half-Yearly Examination and 50% of Annual Examination has been
                                        given towards promotion.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Progress Report should be collected and signed by the parents/legal guardian.
                                        Report Book should be returned within a week of its issue. The result declared
                                        at the end of the year is final and not reconsidered. Answer papers of the final
                                        examination are not shown.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Co-curricular activities must be attended. This will be considered a regular
                                        subject which will have reflection in promotion.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </ul>

                            <div class="text-center mt-4 pt-3 border-top">
                                <button onclick="toggleList(this)" class="btn btn-navy rounded-pill px-4 shadow-sm">
                                    Read All Rules <i class="bi bi-chevron-down ms-2"></i>
                                </button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div id="parents" class="rule-card mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                        <div class="rule-header">
                            <span class="rule-num">03</span>
                            <h3>Parents/Local Guardian</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="rule-body">
                            <ul class="rules-list mb-0">
                                <li>Special attention is given to ensure a high standard of morality and discipline.
                                    Guardians are requested to co-operate with the efforts of the school authorities.
                                </li>

                                <li>By ensuring that their wards are punctual and regular in attendance.</li>

                                <li>By ensuring that ward’s clothes and person are neat and clean.</li>

                                <div class="hidden-li-content" style="display: none;">
                                    <li>By following up to monthly report which keeps them informed of their ward’s
                                        progress.</li>

                                    <li>By ensuring that their wards in calendar the lesson given and the tasks set
                                        every day and that do the home work properly.</li>

                                    <li>By checking regularly the absence record in this diary to make sure that all
                                        signatures are genuine.</li>

                                    <li>By meeting the Headmaster whenever asked for.</li>

                                    <li>Parents who accompany their wards should take them back as soon as the classes
                                        are dispersed.</li>

                                    <li>Only Nursery, K.G.-I & K.G.-II children’s parents may come inside the school
                                        premises to leave wards for the first month. Others should escort their wards
                                        only upto the gate. Only parents who wish to meet the Principal may come to the
                                        office as per visiting hour.</li>

                                    <li>Parents and guardians should never walk on the verandah or enter the class room,
                                        interview the teachers during the working hour without obtaining prior
                                        permission from the Principal.</li>

                                    <li>The result of the annual examination of the defaulters will not be published.
                                        All dues should be paid before commencement of the Annual Examination.</li>
                                </div>
                            </ul>

                            <div class="text-center mt-4 pt-3 border-top">
                                <button onclick="toggleList(this)"
                                    class="btn btn-navy rounded-pill px-4 shadow-sm rulesBtn">
                                    Read All Rules <i class="bi bi-chevron-down ms-2"></i>
                                </button>
                            </div>

                        </div>

                        <div id="attendance" class="rule-card mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                            <div class="rule-header">
                                <span class="rule-num">02</span>
                                <h3>Attendance & Leave</h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="rule-body">
                                <p>A minimum of <strong>75% attendance</strong> is mandatory for promotion to the next
                                    class.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Leave applications must be submitted in advance via the parent portal.</li>
                                    <li>Medical leave for more than 3 days requires a valid doctor's certificate.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div id="#discipline" class="rule-card mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                            <div class="rule-header">
                                <span class="rule-num">03</span>
                                <h3>Discipline Policy</h3>
                            </div>
                            <div class="rule-body">
                                <p class="text-danger fw-bold"><i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill"></i> Zero
                                    Tolerance Policy:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Bullying, physical violence, or use of foul language will result in immediate
                                        suspension.</li>
                                    <li>Electronic gadgets (phones, tablets) are strictly prohibited unless requested by
                                        a
                                        teacher.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div id="general" class="rule-card mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                                <div class="rule-header">
                                    <span class="rule-num">01</span>
                                    <h3>Transport Rules</h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="rule-body">
                                    <ul class="rules-list mb-0">
                                        <li>School bus service is an optional facility. Parents or guardians are free to choose this facility or not at the time of admission or at the renewal time.</li>

<li>Admission to the school does not mean an automatic permission to avail the school bus service. It has to be independently applied for at the time of fresh admission or at the renewal time in the prescribed form. Only students formally admitted to the school are eligible for availing the bus service. The school bus is meant only for the school children. Parents or guardians shall not board the bus so as not to cause inconvenience to the students.</li>

<li>To start the bus service, students need to fill a registration form with a fee of Rs. 100/-.</li>

                                        <div class="hidden-li-content" style="display: none;">
                                           <li>To discontinue the bus service, students are required to submit an application with a charge of Rs. 150/-.</li>

<li>Twelve months bus fare is applicable.</li>

<li>If any student is found without registration for bus service, he or she will be fined Rs. 1000/-.</li>

<li>Parents or guardians are not allowed in the bus.</li>

<li>The school bus service is facilitated by the school for the convenience of students and their parents. It is an optional facility and the cost involved in running this service should be borne entirely by those availing the service.</li>

<li>The buses shall not stop other than the points specified in the bus application form.</li>

<li>Pupils whose dues or school bus fare are not cleared completely will be barred from sitting for examinations.</li>

<li>For all information, complaints of disciplinary nature or minor discomforts related to the bus, parents or guardians may contact the Principal or the school office.</li>

<li>Parents should bring their children on time at the specified bus points only for boarding the school bus and should also be present on time to receive them.</li>

<li>Parents or guardians must ensure that under no circumstances the school bus is boarded by their ward suffering from contagious or infectious diseases.</li>

<li>The school bus is available on the routes mentioned on the Bus Route Notice Board. If a route is not viable financially or due to non-availability of buses or parking, the service of that route may be discontinued with a notice of one month. No change of route will be made unless a decision is taken by the school authorities.</li>

<li>The school will not be responsible for students travelling by their own transport.</li>

<li>Unruly behaviour like moving about, shrieking, shouting, or standing near the gate is not acceptable and may lead to suspension from availing the school bus.</li>

<li>In case of emergency, parents are requested to get in touch with the school authorities immediately.</li>

<li>The contact numbers are: 8638769734, 6001570583.</li>
                                        </div>
                                    </ul>

                                    <div class="text-center mt-4 pt-3 border-top">
                                        <button onclick="toggleList(this)"
                                            class="btn btn-navy rounded-pill px-4 shadow-sm rulesBtn">
                                            Read All Rules <i class="bi bi-chevron-down ms-2"></i>
                                        </button>
                                    </div>

                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
    </section>


    <script>
        function toggleList(btn) {
            // Find the rule-card instead of the missing wrapper class
            const wrapper = btn.closest('.rule-card');
            const content = wrapper.querySelector('.hidden-li-content');

            if (content.style.display === "none") {
                content.style.display = "block";
                btn.innerHTML = 'Show Less <i class="bi bi-chevron-up ms-2"></i>';
                // Ensure these classes exist in your CSS
                btn.classList.add('btn-outline-navy');
                btn.classList.remove('btn-navy');
            } else {
                content.style.display = "none";
                btn.innerHTML = 'Read All Rules <i class="bi bi-chevron-down ms-2"></i>';
                btn.classList.add('btn-navy');
                btn.classList.remove('btn-outline-navy');
            }
        }
    </script>